1
00:00:07,610 --> 00:00:09,320
Earth,

2
00:00:09,320 --> 00:00:11,290
fire,

3
00:00:11,290 --> 00:00:12,690
air,

4
00:00:12,690 --> 00:00:14,930
water...

5
00:00:14,930 --> 00:00:19,060
Only the Avatar can
master all four elements

6
00:00:19,060 --> 00:00:22,070
and bring balance to the world.

7
00:00:22,070 --> 00:00:25,070
[Dramatic music]

8
00:00:27,210 --> 00:00:29,470
Six months ago, Avatar Korra defeated

9
00:00:29,480 --> 00:00:31,140
Amon and The Equalists.

10
00:00:31,140 --> 00:00:33,110
Since then, the council was disbanded

11
00:00:33,110 --> 00:00:35,910
and the united Republic
elected its first president.

12
00:00:35,920 --> 00:00:37,920
Tenzin's brother, commander Bumi,

13
00:00:37,920 --> 00:00:40,450
retired and moved to air temple island.

14
00:00:40,450 --> 00:00:42,320
And Korra and her boyfriend, Mako,

15
00:00:42,320 --> 00:00:43,750
have been the talk of the town.

16
00:00:43,760 --> 00:00:45,520
Peace has come to Republic city,

17
00:00:45,520 --> 00:00:47,360
but unbeknownst to the Avatar,

18
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:49,930
danger now threatens
the Southern water tribe.

19
00:00:49,930 --> 00:00:51,330
[Horn blares]

20
00:00:51,330 --> 00:00:53,330
This your first watch?

21
00:00:53,330 --> 00:00:54,500
Mm-hmm.

22
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:56,330
Well then, you'd better keep

23
00:00:56,340 --> 00:00:57,940
your eyes peeled, laddie.

24
00:00:57,940 --> 00:01:01,640
You never know what creatures
lurk in the murky depths.

25
00:01:01,640 --> 00:01:03,610
[Gasps] [Thunder rumbling]

26
00:01:03,610 --> 00:01:06,180
[Chuckling]

27
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:12,520
Uh, sir.

28
00:01:12,520 --> 00:01:14,080
What?

29
00:01:14,090 --> 00:01:15,350
Aah!

30
00:01:15,350 --> 00:01:18,360
Man overboard! Man overboard!

31
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:27,900
[Bell dings]

32
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:31,130
It's pro-bending night in Republic City,

33
00:01:31,140 --> 00:01:33,670
and have we got a doozy for you.

34
00:01:33,670 --> 00:01:35,370
Fan favorites, the fire ferrets,

35
00:01:35,370 --> 00:01:37,340
are about to take on hot newcomers,

36
00:01:37,340 --> 00:01:39,110
the rhino-lions.

37
00:01:39,110 --> 00:01:41,610
Now we all know that our
last match was garbage.

38
00:01:41,610 --> 00:01:42,750
Terrible.

39
00:01:42,750 --> 00:01:44,280
Even Pabu could have done a better job.

40
00:01:44,280 --> 00:01:45,280
[Pabu chitters]

41
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:46,750
But that's in the past,

42
00:01:46,750 --> 00:01:49,050
because when you back a
fire ferret in the corner,

43
00:01:49,050 --> 00:01:51,020
well, mister, he comes out fighting!

44
00:01:51,020 --> 00:01:52,060
[Pabu hisses]

45
00:01:52,060 --> 00:01:54,060
So let's get out there

46
00:01:54,060 --> 00:01:55,890
and bend like there's no tomorrow.

47
00:01:55,900 --> 00:01:58,260
Are you with me?

48
00:01:58,260 --> 00:02:00,100
[Sniffs]

49
00:02:02,070 --> 00:02:04,330
[Bell dings]

50
00:02:04,340 --> 00:02:05,870
[All grunt] [Buzzer]

51
00:02:05,870 --> 00:02:08,370
Ooh, the fire ferrets go down in the water

52
00:02:08,370 --> 00:02:09,940
and right into the record books

53
00:02:09,940 --> 00:02:12,840
for the fastest knockout
in pro-bending history.

54
00:02:12,850 --> 00:02:15,610
Where's Mako when I need him?

55
00:02:15,610 --> 00:02:20,720
[Sirens wail, motorcycle revs]

56
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:23,890
[Tires squeal]

57
00:02:23,890 --> 00:02:29,830
[Sirens wail]

58
00:02:34,370 --> 00:02:35,770
[Motorcycle revs]

59
00:02:39,600 --> 00:02:41,940
[Gasps]

60
00:02:47,180 --> 00:02:49,110
[Truck honks]

61
00:02:54,020 --> 00:02:55,320
[Tires screech]

62
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:57,520
[Explosion]

63
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:59,560
[Tires screeching]

64
00:03:04,530 --> 00:03:06,930
[Men groan]

65
00:03:06,930 --> 00:03:09,770
Looks like you had some car trouble.

66
00:03:09,770 --> 00:03:13,300
Good thing the police are here.

67
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:26,250
I think these planes are
finally ready to ship.

68
00:03:26,250 --> 00:03:28,920
I hate to mention the
elephant-rhino in the room,

69
00:03:28,920 --> 00:03:31,020
but since your father was thrown in prison,

70
00:03:31,020 --> 00:03:32,890
no company will work with us.

71
00:03:32,890 --> 00:03:34,590
We're nearly bankrupt.

72
00:03:34,590 --> 00:03:35,930
Don't worry.

73
00:03:35,930 --> 00:03:36,930
I'm going to the South pole

74
00:03:36,930 --> 00:03:38,300
to meet with someone who can help us

75
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:41,400
put Future Industries back on top.

76
00:03:45,340 --> 00:03:48,540
[Oogi grumbles]

77
00:03:55,980 --> 00:03:57,980
Wah!

78
00:04:13,670 --> 00:04:15,630
[Coughs]

79
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:18,570
The Avatar is the winner!

80
00:04:19,640 --> 00:04:21,270
No fair.

81
00:04:21,270 --> 00:04:23,740
You can't go into the Avatar state to win.

82
00:04:23,740 --> 00:04:25,510
- [Raspberries]
- You did what?

83
00:04:25,510 --> 00:04:30,450
The Avatar state is not to
be used as a booster rocket.

84
00:04:30,450 --> 00:04:32,480
You are toying with a dangerous power

85
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:34,150
that you obviously do not appreciate.

86
00:04:34,150 --> 00:04:37,320
It's the "Avatar state,"
and I'm the Avatar.

87
00:04:37,320 --> 00:04:39,090
Who appreciates it more than me?

88
00:04:39,090 --> 00:04:41,290
Clearly, you need more training to grasp

89
00:04:41,290 --> 00:04:43,930
the depths of your spiritual connections,

90
00:04:43,930 --> 00:04:46,060
not to mention that you're still a long way

91
00:04:46,070 --> 00:04:47,630
from mastering air-bending.

92
00:04:47,630 --> 00:04:49,830
I have mastered air-bending.

93
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:52,270
Punch, punch, punch!

94
00:04:52,270 --> 00:04:54,540
See? Mastered.

95
00:04:54,540 --> 00:04:56,470
- Looks pretty good to me.
- [Sighs]

96
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:58,710
Is it too late for you to un-retire

97
00:04:58,710 --> 00:05:00,240
from the united forces?

98
00:05:00,250 --> 00:05:02,780
The paperwork's gone
through, little brother.

99
00:05:02,780 --> 00:05:07,150
From now on, it's 24/7 Bumi time!

100
00:05:08,820 --> 00:05:11,490
You've mastered Korra-style air-bending.

101
00:05:11,490 --> 00:05:14,660
Now you need to master real air-bending.

102
00:05:14,660 --> 00:05:17,260
Hopefully, our visit to
all of the air temples

103
00:05:17,260 --> 00:05:19,130
will give you the inspiration you need

104
00:05:19,130 --> 00:05:22,070
to delve more deeply into your studies.

105
00:05:22,070 --> 00:05:23,530
Can we see where grandpa Aang was born?

106
00:05:23,540 --> 00:05:25,270
How many lemurs can I have?

107
00:05:25,270 --> 00:05:27,200
I want to get tattoos,
but instead of arrows,

108
00:05:27,210 --> 00:05:28,540
I want lightning bolts.

109
00:05:28,540 --> 00:05:30,070
You can't get lightning bolts.

110
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,610
That doesn't make any sense.

111
00:05:31,610 --> 00:05:33,440
You don't make any sense!

112
00:05:33,450 --> 00:05:34,810
Fight, fight, fight!

113
00:05:34,810 --> 00:05:36,850
[Both grumbling] No one's fighting.

114
00:05:36,850 --> 00:05:39,420
We're going to have a wonderful time.

115
00:05:39,420 --> 00:05:40,820
[Groans]

116
00:05:40,820 --> 00:05:43,150
Now that the president is in office

117
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:44,790
and I'm not needed on the council,

118
00:05:44,790 --> 00:05:46,890
I can finally relax with my family

119
00:05:46,890 --> 00:05:49,260
and give Korra the attention she needs.

120
00:05:49,260 --> 00:05:51,230
Great. More attention.

121
00:05:51,230 --> 00:05:53,360
[Laughs] Relax?

122
00:05:53,370 --> 00:05:55,270
I'd pay money to see that.

123
00:05:55,270 --> 00:05:59,400
Maybe I'll tag along just
to see "Vacation Tenzin."

124
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,340
You're not invited.

125
00:06:01,340 --> 00:06:03,510
Before we go on your dad's study trip,

126
00:06:03,510 --> 00:06:05,910
we're going to have some
real fun in my hometown

127
00:06:05,910 --> 00:06:07,440
at the glacier spirits festival.

128
00:06:07,450 --> 00:06:08,850
They've got rides, games,

129
00:06:08,850 --> 00:06:10,880
and all kinds of fried food on sticks.

130
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:12,850
All: Yay!

131
00:06:12,850 --> 00:06:13,880
[Excitedly chattering]

132
00:06:13,890 --> 00:06:16,720
Yep, there's vacation Tenzin.

133
00:06:16,720 --> 00:06:19,390
And you can't stop me
from going to the festival.

134
00:06:19,390 --> 00:06:22,360
Mom already invited me.

135
00:06:22,360 --> 00:06:25,360
[Horn blares]

136
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:27,060
[Chuckles]

137
00:06:27,070 --> 00:06:28,370
So I walk up and say,

138
00:06:28,370 --> 00:06:31,030
"looks like you had some car trouble.

139
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:33,200
Good thing the police are here."

140
00:06:33,210 --> 00:06:35,940
[Laughs] Did you write that beforehand?

141
00:06:35,940 --> 00:06:39,380
Yeah, I had a few others. Let's see, uh...

142
00:06:39,380 --> 00:06:43,410
"Looks like you guys should
put more 'try' in triad," huh?

143
00:06:43,420 --> 00:06:47,950
Or, "when you get to jail,
tell 'em Mako sent ya."

144
00:06:47,950 --> 00:06:49,550
Ooh, I like that one.

145
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:52,420
Okay, I'll use that next time.

146
00:06:52,420 --> 00:06:55,730
Beifong says if I keep it up,
I could make detective soon.

147
00:06:55,730 --> 00:06:57,560
Oh, that sounds so fun.

148
00:06:57,560 --> 00:06:59,600
All I do is train all day.

149
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:03,400
It's like Tenzin's totally
forgotten how I beat Amon.

150
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,100
Tenzin's just trying to help you become

151
00:07:05,100 --> 00:07:07,140
the best Avatar you can be.

152
00:07:07,140 --> 00:07:08,940
Of course you'd take his side.

153
00:07:08,940 --> 00:07:10,670
I'm not taking his side. I'm just...

154
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:13,610
I'm gonna take a walk.

155
00:07:15,180 --> 00:07:17,750
Why is it so much easier to bust triads

156
00:07:17,750 --> 00:07:22,750
than it is to get through one
conversation with my girlfriend?

157
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:26,790
Grangran!

158
00:07:26,790 --> 00:07:30,130
Oh, you've all gotten so big.

159
00:07:30,130 --> 00:07:31,730
We missed you, aunt Kya.

160
00:07:31,730 --> 00:07:34,160
Oh, I missed you too.

161
00:07:34,170 --> 00:07:37,000
Your father doesn't bring
you to visit nearly enough.

162
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:39,140
He's probably scared I'll beat him up

163
00:07:39,140 --> 00:07:40,200
like when we were kids.

164
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:42,570
I'm not scared of you...

165
00:07:42,570 --> 00:07:45,740
Anymore.

166
00:07:45,740 --> 00:07:47,880
- You remember Mako.
- Sir.

167
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:49,810
I hope you're not getting my daughter

168
00:07:49,820 --> 00:07:51,980
into any more trouble up in the city.

169
00:07:51,980 --> 00:07:55,590
Uh, no. I, uh... no.

170
00:07:55,590 --> 00:07:58,660
- Knock it off, dad.
- [Chuckles]

171
00:07:58,660 --> 00:08:00,220
Wow, look at all these people

172
00:08:00,230 --> 00:08:01,460
that came out to greet us.

173
00:08:01,460 --> 00:08:04,460
Uh, no. They came to greet them.

174
00:08:04,460 --> 00:08:08,630
[Cheers and applause]

175
00:08:08,630 --> 00:08:11,840
The great chief of the Northern water tribe

176
00:08:11,840 --> 00:08:14,300
comes to grace us with his presence.

177
00:08:14,310 --> 00:08:15,770
[Mockingly] Hooray.

178
00:08:15,770 --> 00:08:17,210
Just relax, Tonraq.

179
00:08:17,210 --> 00:08:19,040
He'll be gone soon enough.

180
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,740
[Grumbles]

181
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:23,480
[Bird squawks]

182
00:08:28,420 --> 00:08:32,220
Whoa, who are the lovely ladies?

183
00:08:32,220 --> 00:08:34,930
That's Eska and Desna,
the chief's children.

184
00:08:34,930 --> 00:08:36,490
Desna is a guy.

185
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:39,630
[Laughs] Oh, no, sure. I knew that.

186
00:08:39,630 --> 00:08:41,870
And which one is Desna?

187
00:08:43,400 --> 00:08:46,040
Good to see you again, Avatar Korra.

188
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:47,700
Good to see you too.

189
00:08:47,710 --> 00:08:49,470
Tonraq.

190
00:08:49,470 --> 00:08:52,640
Brother.

191
00:08:59,860 --> 00:09:02,220
It's a shame the southerners have abandoned

192
00:09:02,230 --> 00:09:04,230
all connections to the spirits,

193
00:09:04,230 --> 00:09:06,460
even during the most hallowed times.

194
00:09:06,460 --> 00:09:08,700
I've always loved the
glacier spirits festival.

195
00:09:08,700 --> 00:09:10,300
It's fun.

196
00:09:10,300 --> 00:09:12,070
This festival used to be a solemn time

197
00:09:12,070 --> 00:09:14,000
of fasting and meditation.

198
00:09:14,010 --> 00:09:16,310
Now it's just a chance to watch some rube

199
00:09:16,310 --> 00:09:18,910
try to stick an entire
arctic hen in his mouth.

200
00:09:18,910 --> 00:09:22,610
[Muffled] Wha... what? It's so good.

201
00:09:22,610 --> 00:09:24,650
Traditions change.

202
00:09:24,650 --> 00:09:27,320
It's not the end of the world.

203
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:29,220
Tell that to the sailors
who are being attacked

204
00:09:29,220 --> 00:09:31,890
by angry spirits in Southern waters.

205
00:09:31,890 --> 00:09:34,120
Some traditions have purpose.

206
00:09:34,130 --> 00:09:37,160
Wait, spirits are attacking ships?

207
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:40,830
I'm surprised the Avatar
doesn't know about that.

208
00:09:40,830 --> 00:09:42,470
Apparently you haven't been given

209
00:09:42,470 --> 00:09:44,100
all the information you need.

210
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:46,270
It would be my honor to instruct you

211
00:09:46,270 --> 00:09:48,400
in the spiritual ways of the water tribe.

212
00:09:48,410 --> 00:09:50,940
I wouldn't mind learning
about fighting spirits.

213
00:09:50,940 --> 00:09:53,210
Air-bending is getting pretty boring.

214
00:09:53,210 --> 00:09:55,080
Tenzin is Korra's instructor.

215
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:57,480
He can give her all the training she needs.

216
00:09:57,480 --> 00:10:00,420
So you've said.

217
00:10:03,590 --> 00:10:05,290
I'm glad you came with me to this meeting.

218
00:10:05,290 --> 00:10:07,960
Varrick is one of the
richest men in the world,

219
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:11,290
and he controls the entire
global shipping business.

220
00:10:11,300 --> 00:10:13,330
So you're my assistant.

221
00:10:13,330 --> 00:10:15,430
Just stand there and don't say anything.

222
00:10:15,430 --> 00:10:16,830
[Pabu chitters] No problem.

223
00:10:16,830 --> 00:10:19,240
Pabu and I are natural assistants.

224
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:21,640
Man, this is nice.

225
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:24,310
I gotta get into this
whole "business" thing.

226
00:10:31,280 --> 00:10:33,880
Did you see that? Levitation!

227
00:10:33,890 --> 00:10:36,450
[Laughs] I was a foot off the ground.

228
00:10:36,450 --> 00:10:37,820
Is that incredible or what?

229
00:10:37,820 --> 00:10:39,520
How does he do that?

230
00:10:39,520 --> 00:10:41,190
- That's unbelievable.
- That's amazing.

231
00:10:41,190 --> 00:10:42,560
What?

232
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:44,990
It looked like you were
just sitting on a pillow.

233
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,000
[Gasps]

234
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,930
[All gasp]

235
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:52,330
Are you saying I wasn't levitating?

236
00:10:52,340 --> 00:10:56,170
[Gulps] Uh, no?

237
00:10:56,170 --> 00:10:57,710
Well, why didn't anyone tell me?

238
00:10:57,710 --> 00:10:59,780
Now I look like an idiot!

239
00:10:59,780 --> 00:11:02,710
Swami, you're fired!

240
00:11:07,580 --> 00:11:08,820
- Aah!
- I like you, kid.

241
00:11:08,820 --> 00:11:10,690
You're a real straight
shooter, just like me.

242
00:11:10,690 --> 00:11:12,920
- Ms. Sato? He's with you?
- Mm-hmm.

243
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:16,160
Brought your tiger-shark
with you to do business, huh?

244
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:18,560
Now that's moxie. [Laughs]

245
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:20,360
Get over here and pop a squat.

246
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:22,670
Zhu li, get some tea for my guests.

247
00:11:22,670 --> 00:11:24,570
Thank you for meeting with me.

248
00:11:24,570 --> 00:11:27,240
As you know, future industries
is looking for a partner

249
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:28,670
- to handle our shipping...
- Sure.

250
00:11:28,670 --> 00:11:29,940
But first, you gotta check out

251
00:11:29,940 --> 00:11:32,910
my new venture: Moving pictures.

252
00:11:32,910 --> 00:11:35,310
Zhu li, do the thing.

253
00:11:37,380 --> 00:11:39,980
You're gonna love this.

254
00:11:45,490 --> 00:11:47,290
Mind-blowing, right?

255
00:11:47,290 --> 00:11:49,730
- Yeah.
- Now, forget that!

256
00:11:49,730 --> 00:11:53,060
That's the past! Shut it off, Zhu li!

257
00:11:53,060 --> 00:11:54,300
Imagine watching this.

258
00:11:54,300 --> 00:11:56,200
Ginger, come over here and do your poses.

259
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:58,200
[Gasps]

260
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:01,200
[Sultry music]

261
00:12:01,210 --> 00:12:04,040
â™ª

262
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:05,770
Spectacular.

263
00:12:05,780 --> 00:12:07,280
And we tell a story.

264
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:08,740
There's romance, action,

265
00:12:08,750 --> 00:12:10,480
some funny animal stuff for the kids.

266
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:11,480
You know, whatever.

267
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:13,880
Thanks, Ginger. Go rest your gams.

268
00:12:13,880 --> 00:12:16,690
How about that, tiger-shark?

269
00:12:16,690 --> 00:12:17,950
We're gonna do big business

270
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:20,360
with these "movers," as I call 'em.

271
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:22,120
Okay.

272
00:12:22,130 --> 00:12:23,290
But I'm just concentrating

273
00:12:23,290 --> 00:12:25,390
on getting future industries back on track.

274
00:12:25,400 --> 00:12:26,660
If we could hammer out a deal...

275
00:12:26,660 --> 00:12:28,130
Stop.

276
00:12:28,130 --> 00:12:31,070
Look me in the eye.

277
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:36,610
We got a deal!

278
00:12:36,610 --> 00:12:40,740
[All cheering]

279
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:43,850
We'll hammer out the details
at the royal feast tonight.

280
00:12:43,850 --> 00:12:46,750
Now who wants a rocket-boat ride?

281
00:12:46,750 --> 00:12:49,590
[All cheering]

282
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:54,390
Is that how business usually goes?

283
00:12:54,390 --> 00:12:57,190
<i>You are a natural assistant.</i>

284
00:13:01,630 --> 00:13:04,430
This is a wonderful feast
in your honor, Uncle.

285
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:06,070
This is nothing.

286
00:13:06,070 --> 00:13:07,570
When this festival was founded,

287
00:13:07,570 --> 00:13:09,970
the tribal elders would
commune with the spirits.

288
00:13:09,970 --> 00:13:12,440
People would watch the
brilliant displays of light

289
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:14,280
as spirits danced in the sky.

290
00:13:14,280 --> 00:13:16,780
Wow. I've never seen that.

291
00:13:16,780 --> 00:13:18,410
And that is a shame,

292
00:13:18,420 --> 00:13:20,020
since the Avatar is the bridge

293
00:13:20,020 --> 00:13:22,720
between the material world and the spirits.

294
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:25,620
That is why I want so badly to teach you,

295
00:13:25,620 --> 00:13:27,360
to help you fulfill your destiny.

296
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:29,360
I thought I had made it clear

297
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:31,630
that Tenzin is teaching her.

298
00:13:31,630 --> 00:13:36,230
Every Avatar before you
traveled the world to learn.

299
00:13:36,230 --> 00:13:39,130
It was Tenzin and your
father who kept you secluded

300
00:13:39,140 --> 00:13:40,470
at the South pole.

301
00:13:40,470 --> 00:13:42,640
I thought Aang ordered the white lotus

302
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:43,970
to keep me down here?

303
00:13:43,970 --> 00:13:47,540
We all did what we
thought was best for you.

304
00:13:47,550 --> 00:13:50,510
Who I train with should
be my decision, dad,

305
00:13:50,510 --> 00:13:53,220
not yours or Tenzin's.

306
00:13:53,220 --> 00:13:56,120
Looks like someone's
trying to take your place

307
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:58,920
as the Avatar's stick-in-the-mud mentor.

308
00:13:58,920 --> 00:14:00,720
Bumi, don't pick on Tenzin.

309
00:14:00,730 --> 00:14:02,660
You know he's always been sensitive.

310
00:14:02,660 --> 00:14:04,990
I'm not sensitive!

311
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:09,100
[Both laughing]

312
00:14:09,100 --> 00:14:12,200
As your chief, it is my honor to speak

313
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:14,440
at this festival, which was founded

314
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:16,240
to bring our tribes together

315
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:17,940
and restore the ancient balance

316
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:20,840
between our world and that of the spirits.

317
00:14:20,850 --> 00:14:24,780
But I am saddened to
see what it has become...

318
00:14:24,780 --> 00:14:28,720
A cheap carnival that celebrates
greedy and trivial humans.

319
00:14:28,720 --> 00:14:30,290
[Teeth squeaking]

320
00:14:30,290 --> 00:14:32,520
I fear the time is fast approaching

321
00:14:32,520 --> 00:14:34,990
when the North can no longer stand idly by

322
00:14:34,990 --> 00:14:39,900
while our Southern brothers
slip into total spiritual decay.

323
00:14:39,900 --> 00:14:43,370
Angry spirits are already
attacking ships in your waters.

324
00:14:43,370 --> 00:14:47,800
I only hope we are not
too late to change course.

325
00:14:47,810 --> 00:14:51,070
[All murmuring]

326
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:52,810
Chief Unalaq, everybody.

327
00:14:52,810 --> 00:14:54,110
Always great to have him in town.

328
00:14:54,110 --> 00:14:55,380
Now let's have some fun

329
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:58,450
with wacky wushu's dancin' otter-penguins.

330
00:14:58,450 --> 00:15:01,450
[Energetic music]

331
00:15:01,450 --> 00:15:01,950
â™ª

332
00:15:06,960 --> 00:15:09,990
[Carnival music]

333
00:15:09,990 --> 00:15:12,960
[Giggles]

334
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:16,300
Mm-mm.

335
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:22,600
[Clears throat]

336
00:15:22,610 --> 00:15:25,870
Wish me luck. I'm making my move.

337
00:15:25,880 --> 00:15:27,280
Whee!

338
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:28,610
Good luck.

339
00:15:28,610 --> 00:15:30,680
Those two have always creeped me out.

340
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:32,950
They smell like a grandma's attic.

341
00:15:32,950 --> 00:15:35,980
Hey, I'm Bolin. I'm a friend of Korra's.

342
00:15:35,990 --> 00:15:37,420
You're Eska, right?

343
00:15:37,420 --> 00:15:40,460
Wow, I'm just... I'm loving these robes.

344
00:15:40,460 --> 00:15:41,960
[Hisses]

345
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:43,860
[Clears throat]

346
00:15:43,860 --> 00:15:47,760
So you are from the North, right? Cool.

347
00:15:47,770 --> 00:15:48,760
That's like... you know, that's, like,

348
00:15:48,770 --> 00:15:49,970
my favorite direction.

349
00:15:49,970 --> 00:15:52,030
I think he is trying to establish

350
00:15:52,040 --> 00:15:53,440
some kind of bond with you

351
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:55,800
based on your geographic point of origin.

352
00:15:55,810 --> 00:15:57,310
Perhaps it would be interesting

353
00:15:57,310 --> 00:15:58,770
to spend time with a person

354
00:15:58,780 --> 00:16:01,510
whose ways are so rough and uncultured.

355
00:16:01,510 --> 00:16:04,280
You amuse me. I will make you mine.

356
00:16:04,280 --> 00:16:07,850
You mean like a boyfriend
or... or like a slave?

357
00:16:07,850 --> 00:16:09,450
Yes.

358
00:16:09,450 --> 00:16:13,490
Win me prizes. [Laughs nervously]

359
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:16,120
[Bell dings]

360
00:16:16,130 --> 00:16:17,790
Unalaq offered to train me.

361
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:19,530
He says he can teach me about the spirits

362
00:16:19,530 --> 00:16:20,630
and my connection to them.

363
00:16:20,630 --> 00:16:23,800
Sounds good. What does Tenzin think?

364
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:25,630
Tenzin thinks I'm his prisoner

365
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:27,040
or one of his kids.

366
00:16:27,040 --> 00:16:29,340
I'll never finish training
with him in charge.

367
00:16:31,670 --> 00:16:32,710
[Bell dings]

368
00:16:32,710 --> 00:16:35,540
We have a winner.

369
00:16:35,550 --> 00:16:38,050
I mean, you heard what Unalaq said.

370
00:16:38,050 --> 00:16:40,150
The South is spiritually unbalanced,

371
00:16:40,150 --> 00:16:42,380
and it's the Avatar's job to fix it.

372
00:16:42,390 --> 00:16:43,390
But my dad won't even let me

373
00:16:43,390 --> 00:16:46,590
think about Unalaq teaching me.

374
00:16:46,590 --> 00:16:47,760
- Well?
- Well, what?

375
00:16:47,760 --> 00:16:49,760
What do you think I should do?

376
00:16:49,760 --> 00:16:52,430
I guess you should do
what you think is right.

377
00:16:52,430 --> 00:16:54,200
I support whatever decision you make.

378
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:57,030
Oh, thanks. That's a big help.

379
00:16:57,030 --> 00:16:59,430
I thought you wanted me to be supportive.

380
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:01,500
Now you want me to tell you what I think?

381
00:17:01,510 --> 00:17:02,770
Make up your mind.

382
00:17:02,770 --> 00:17:04,670
Oof!

383
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:08,280
Just forget it.

384
00:17:12,950 --> 00:17:15,820
[Bells chiming]

385
00:17:18,420 --> 00:17:19,960
Ugh.

386
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:21,160
Naga, what are you doing?

387
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:22,190
[Naga howling]

388
00:17:22,190 --> 00:17:24,060
Naga, hush.

389
00:17:24,060 --> 00:17:29,670
[Howling continues]

390
00:17:29,670 --> 00:17:32,100
Quiet, Naga. You'll wake everyone up.

391
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:34,200
[Naga howling]

392
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:36,140
[Yawns] What's going on?

393
00:17:40,440 --> 00:17:43,780
What is that?

394
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:46,450
Ugh!

395
00:17:46,450 --> 00:17:49,350
[Groans]

396
00:17:51,650 --> 00:17:53,560
[Spirit growls]

397
00:17:56,350 --> 00:17:58,550
[Groans]

398
00:18:01,990 --> 00:18:04,930
Got it!

399
00:18:04,930 --> 00:18:05,960
Don't got it!

400
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:10,130
[Both groaning]

401
00:18:24,650 --> 00:18:27,050
Korra!

402
00:18:36,360 --> 00:18:38,230
Aah!

403
00:18:38,230 --> 00:18:39,890
[Screams]

404
00:18:39,900 --> 00:18:41,900
[Groans]

405
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:44,030
Aah!

406
00:18:44,030 --> 00:18:46,630
[Groans]

407
00:18:51,770 --> 00:18:55,180
Spirit, why are you angry with us?

408
00:18:55,180 --> 00:18:59,950
What have we done to offend you?

409
00:18:59,950 --> 00:19:01,780
[Groans]

410
00:19:27,310 --> 00:19:29,540
[Grunts]

411
00:19:29,550 --> 00:19:33,650
[Groans]

412
00:20:19,630 --> 00:20:23,000
Go in peace.

413
00:20:26,500 --> 00:20:29,700
Korra, are you all right?

414
00:20:29,710 --> 00:20:31,340
How were you able to control that spirit

415
00:20:31,340 --> 00:20:32,470
when no one else could?

416
00:20:32,470 --> 00:20:33,970
As your father could tell you,

417
00:20:33,980 --> 00:20:36,240
I have spent my life studying the spirits

418
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:38,040
and learning their ways.

419
00:20:38,050 --> 00:20:40,310
All of this knowledge is lost in the South,

420
00:20:40,320 --> 00:20:43,350
but I could teach you everything I know.

421
00:20:43,350 --> 00:20:46,790
Chief Unalaq, clearly,
you are very knowledgeable,

422
00:20:46,790 --> 00:20:49,490
but Korra still has much
to learn about air-bending,

423
00:20:49,490 --> 00:20:52,190
and I hope that going to the air temples

424
00:20:52,190 --> 00:20:54,630
will help her connect
with the past avatars.

425
00:20:54,630 --> 00:20:55,900
Ugh!

426
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:57,960
The air temples will teach her nothing.

427
00:20:57,970 --> 00:21:00,370
Only I can give her the training she needs

428
00:21:00,370 --> 00:21:02,800
to be a complete Avatar.

429
00:21:02,810 --> 00:21:05,010
I've told you that will not happen.

430
00:21:05,010 --> 00:21:06,610
Hey, I'm right here!

431
00:21:06,610 --> 00:21:08,780
Anyone want to ask me what I think?

432
00:21:08,780 --> 00:21:10,340
Korra, please, listen.

433
00:21:10,350 --> 00:21:12,910
I'm tired of listening
to you... both of you.

434
00:21:12,920 --> 00:21:14,580
You keep me locked up,

435
00:21:14,580 --> 00:21:16,120
telling me you know what's best,

436
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:17,520
but both of you were powerless

437
00:21:17,520 --> 00:21:20,520
against the spirit attack.

438
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:25,030
I think it's time I had a new teacher.

439
00:21:25,030 --> 00:21:26,590
Now, Korra...

440
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:27,960
Unalaq has proven he's the only one

441
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:31,630
who knows what I need to learn.

442
00:21:31,630 --> 00:21:33,100
I have to go with him.

443
00:21:33,100 --> 00:21:35,500
Please, I know you're angry,

444
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:37,940
but we've come so far together.

445
00:21:37,940 --> 00:21:40,340
I'm sorry, Tenzin.

446
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:43,080
This is as far as we go.

447
00:21:46,950 --> 00:21:49,180
It has been a pleasure serving you,

448
00:21:49,180 --> 00:21:51,650
Avatar Korra.

449
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:05,470
I think you forgot a couple of things.

450
00:22:05,470 --> 00:22:08,370
Mother, I think I need some time alone

451
00:22:08,370 --> 00:22:09,740
with my family right now.

452
00:22:09,740 --> 00:22:12,070
This is your family, Tenzin.

453
00:22:12,070 --> 00:22:13,410
When you get to be my age,

454
00:22:13,410 --> 00:22:15,280
you'll be thankful for the time you had

455
00:22:15,280 --> 00:22:16,640
with your siblings.

456
00:22:16,650 --> 00:22:19,050
Besides, I think it's important

457
00:22:19,050 --> 00:22:22,580
that you all visit your
father's home together.

458
00:22:22,580 --> 00:22:24,550
Come on, it'll be fun.

459
00:22:24,550 --> 00:22:27,490
I'm dying to see that
laid-back "vacation Tenzin"

460
00:22:27,490 --> 00:22:29,020
I've heard so much about.

461
00:22:29,020 --> 00:22:33,330
All right. Hop on.

462
00:22:33,330 --> 00:22:35,260
I love you, mom.

463
00:22:35,260 --> 00:22:36,760
We'll see you soon.

464
00:22:36,770 --> 00:22:40,130
[Grunts] Oh!

465
00:22:47,170 --> 00:22:49,480
Do you think I did the right thing?

466
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:51,580
[Sighs] I don't know.

467
00:22:51,580 --> 00:22:53,580
I'm sorry, but I'm not very good

468
00:22:53,580 --> 00:22:55,950
at this Avatar counseling thing.

469
00:22:55,950 --> 00:22:58,120
But I know your heart
is in the right place.

470
00:22:58,120 --> 00:23:00,720
You'll just have to trust it.

471
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:09,430
I know this was a hard decision, Korra.

472
00:23:09,430 --> 00:23:11,330
But it was the right one.

473
00:23:11,330 --> 00:23:13,470
Now it is time to put it behind you

474
00:23:13,470 --> 00:23:14,870
and begin your new training.

475
00:23:14,870 --> 00:23:18,140
I have great plans for you.